President Trump addressed the 126th Annual Conference of the International Association of Chiefs of Police in Chicago. He praised law enforcement officers for their dedication and service, and highlighted his administration's efforts to combat violent crime and support police. He also criticized the leadership of Chicago's police department, particularly Superintendent Eddie Johnson, for not doing enough to address the city's high crime rate. President Trump called for stronger action against sanctuary cities and expressed his support for law enforcement officers. He announced the establishment of a new Commission on Law Enforcement and the Administration of Justice to address challenges faced by law enforcement, such as homelessness and mental illness. The President also recognized several police officers for their bravery and heroism in the line of duty.